<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,990,1092]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<collectingCountry box="[189,367,990,1016]" name="French Guiana" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
: Maroni (“ 
<collectingCountry box="[491,589,990,1016]" name="French Guiana" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Guyane</collectingCountry>
, Maroni”). It is not clear whether the 
<typeStatus box="[1033,1084,991,1017]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
specimen was collected in Saint-Laurent-du-Maroni, one of the two sub-prefectures of 
<collectingCountry box="[898,1072,1028,1054]" name="French Guiana" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
or near the Maroni River, a natural border between 
<collectingCountry box="[467,641,1066,1092]" name="French Guiana" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[697,813,1066,1092]" name="Suriname" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Suriname</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
